URC: Ulster vs Cardiff, Friday March 4th, Kingspan Stadium (kick-off 7.35pm, live on RTÉ and Premier Sports) Stewart Moore lines up at fullback for Ulster for their clash at home to Cardiff amid a myriad of fullback absences for the northern province. Mikey Lowry has not been released from Ireland camp, while Jacob Stockdale, Will Addison and Rob Lyttle all remain injured. Robert Baloucoune and James Hume have both been released by Andy Farrell as they make the Ulster starting XV, while Iain Henderson captains the side having missed Ireland’s victory over Italy through Covid. Elsewhere, Nathan Doak and Billy Burns form a familiar halfback pairing with John Cooney on the bench while Jordi Murphy, Marcus Rea and Nick Timoney - the latter also released from the Ireland squad - form the backrow. Duane Vermeulen is among the replacements. Ulster: S Moore; Baloucoune, Hume, McCloskey, Moxham; Burns, Doak; Warwick, Andrew, M Moore; O’Connor, Henderson (c); Murphy, Rea, Timoney. Replacements: Stewart, McGrath, Milasinovich, Carter, Vermeulen, Cooney, Madigan, Sexton.